The website for Restaurant Manager POS, www.rmpos.com, was a low converting site with an extraneous amount of pages that the user could easily get lost in, causing higher abandonment rates. Its non-responsive design and outdated graphics did not speak to it\'92s target audience or one of the products main incentives - that it\'92s easy to use. \
\
I worked as part of a team to develop visitor profiles and uncover core messaging. We surveyed all the pages and pulled out overlaying themes that were present but not concise. We then combined and/or removed expendable pages, providing enough engaging content that the visitor could be informed, but not too much that the visitor could become overwhelmed and lose their path to converting. I updated the graphics and outdated hardware the software was being displayed on. I also designed a more modern theme that better represented the company and product.\
\
Duet was a new product to the market and ASI wanted the two products to be visually related to one another. We also wanted to give users the option to switch between the two websites, if after going through the site, realized they needed what the other product could offer. \
\
We started to create the Duet website, www.duetpos.com, by preparing visitor profiles and buyers journeys. Based on this, the homepage was created to guide the user to learn as much as they could, and finally, guide them to want to speak with a local reseller. Strong visuals including people interacting with the product as well as screenshots showing resolved pain points, aided in this journey. \
