ASI offers two different point of sale software solutions \'97 Restaurant Manager and Duet. ASI\'92s Restaurant Manager has been an established name in the restaurant industry for nearly 30 years. It\'92s a traditional server side point of sale system with an abundance of features. When Duet was introduced as a new tablet/cloud-based system, we wanted to draw on Restaurant Manager\'92s established and trusted brand. \
\
I started by revisiting the Restaurant Manager logo. I wanted to keep the logo easily recognizable to the existing customer base, maintaining the value of 30 years in the industry, but also update it to attract a new generation of customers. I opened up the leading, and used Fruitiger, the font that the company uses in much of it\'92s sales and marketing collateral, for both words in the logo to create a cleaner look. To have the logo stand out more when used in collateral where Frutiger was heavily used, I rounded the letters which created a more unique look.\
\
The circular element had originally been designed to indicate that Restaurant Manager was a complete and feature rich system. With new competition and more feature full products in the market today, ASI has shifted it\'92s messaging to place more emphasis on the local support and service customers receive when working with Restaurant Manager, since it\'92s sold exclusively through local resellers. I used a curved line for reference to the old logo but also to express the connection to customers through their local resellers. \
\
We wanted the Duet brand to be tied to Restaurant Manager but still be able to stand on it\'92s own. As with Restaurant Manager, Duet is sold exclusively through a local reseller channel, and that same connection is made in the Duet logo. I knew I also wanted to include the signature green and blue colors. Splitting the word by two different colors divided it too much, but using the symmetry of the u allowed for a nice application and also brought attention to putting the focus on you, the customer. \
